headline: Polish military slams 'acts of aggression' after Russian drones intruded into its airspace
description: The Polish Air Force fired on 'hostile objects' on Wednesday morning after repeated violations of its airspace by Russia. This is the first time a NATO member has taken such action since the start of the Russian invasion of Ukraine.

description: Donald Trump's move to fire Federal Reserve Governor Lisa Cook was temporarily blocked by a federal judge on Tuesday as Cook challenges her ouster from the central bank.

description: The fall of Prime Minister François Bayrou ushers in a new period of political instability. The French president, widely seen as responsible for the crisis within his own ranks, now faces pressure from the opposition to propose a new candidate for the post of prime minister.
